[1] Cholera - Angola
Date: Tue, 30 May 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: XinHuaNet [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200605/30/eng20060530_269560.html>

The WHO said in Luanda on Mon, 29 May 2006 that a
cholera outbreak in Angola that broke out mid-Feb
2006 has claimed 1514 lives from more than 40 557
cumulative cases.
In its latest update on the epidemic that has
affected 13 of Angola's 18 provinces, the WHO
said that 282 new cases of the disease and 6
deaths were recorded in the last 24 hours.
The province of Luanda, where cholera erupted in
slum districts of the capital on 13 Feb 2006,
continues to bear the brunt of the epidemic and
275 fatalities have occurred from over 20 781
cases.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The new provinces affected since the last ProMED
update are Lunda Norte and Cabinda. They are
mentioned further below. - Mod.LL]
*****
[2] Cholera - Angola (WHO Outbreak Report)
Date: Thu, 25 May 2006
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: WHO Outbreak Reports [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2006_05_25/en/index.html>

As of 23 May 2006, Angola has reported a total of
38 897 cases and 1437 deaths (case fatality rate
(CFR) 3.6 percent). In the last 24 hours, 303 new
cases including 7 deaths have been reported. 12
out of 18 provinces are affected; of all cases,
51 percent have occurred in Luanda and 19 percent
in Benguela province.
[For epidemiology map, see
<http://www.who.int/entity/csr/don/Angola_Cholera2005_05_25.jpg> - Mod.LL]
The 1st reports from Lunda-Norte province show a
total of 159 cumulative cases and 52 deaths since
the beginning of May 2006. The CFR, broken down
by province, ranges between 1 and 30 percent.
Although current trends show a decline in Luanda
and Benguela provinces, a daily incidence of
around 300 cases is still being reported.
[For epicurve, see
<http://www.who.int/entity/csr/don/epicurve2005_05_25.jpg>
- Mod.LL]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The province of Lunda Norte is located in the
northeast corner of the country. It is the
furthest east that the Angolan outbreak has
reached. The province borders on Congo DR. For a
map showing the borders, see
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>
- Mod.LL]
