[4] Cholera - Angola (Cabinda)
Date: Sat, 27 May 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=443708>

The result of the test on the samples sent to
Luanda on Mon, 29 May 2006 have confirmed the
presence of _Vibrio cholerae_ in Angola's
northern Cabinda province, Angop learned Sat, 27
Sat 2006.
The information was released by the provincial
director of the health services, Luis Kitembo,
who said his department has put in place the
measures to arrest the spread of the disease. To
that effect, the provincial government appointed
a commission to follow up the evolution of the
epidemics. It is coordinated by the governor
himself, Anibal Rocha, assisted by his deputy,
Feliciano Lopes Toco, and includes Luis Kitembo.
Prior to Fri, 26 May 2006, 18 suspected cases of
cholera had been notified in Cabinda, with 1
death. The first case was recorded on 6 May 2006.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Cabinda is a small province separated from Zaire
province and the country per se by the part of
Congo DR that reaches the Atlantic Ocean.
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf> - Mod.LL]
