[6] Cholera - Tanzania (Zanzibar)
Date: Mon, 29 May 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: XinHuaNet [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200605/29/eng20060529_269296.html>

2 more people have fallen victim to cholera in
Zanzibar to bring the total number of deaths to
24 since the outbreak of the epidemic in the
Indian Ocean archipelago in March 2006.
Zanzibar chief medical officer Omar Mohamed
Suleiman said that the new cholera deaths had
been registered in Unguja, the main island of the
archipelago. More than 310 people have been
treated for cholera-like symptoms of vomiting and
diarrhea in Zanzibar since Mar 2006, according to
the medical officer.
Zanzibar experienced 2 severe outbreaks of
cholera back in 1978 and 1997. More than 150
people died of the disease in 1997 alone.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Tanzania showing the relationship of
this semiautonomous archipelago to mainland
Tanzania can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/tanzania.pdf>
- Mod.LL]
